init_text:
Is Listening to a Book Just as Good as Reading It?

Do you listen to audiobooks? What are the benefits, in your opinion, of listening instead of reading? Are there advantages to reading that cannot be gained by listening? Which method do you prefer? Why?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Although reading has its advantages, listening to an audiobook is great for long commutes, when you have time to exercise, and when you're doing

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: This is what makes someone love a book or wonder at it after the fact.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: In fact many people may grow up listening to audiobooks before they ever read a book.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So in a way audiobooks can give a boost to reading by introducing people to the experience.
